1
00:00:03,440 --> 00:00:04,880
You look great.

2
00:00:06,400 --> 00:00:07,240
Thanks.

3
00:00:07,320 --> 00:00:08,680
No, thank you.

4
00:00:09,240 --> 00:00:11,560
Where are we going today?
-To Grandma's.

5
00:00:11,640 --> 00:00:12,920
We'll leave you at Grandma's.

6
00:00:13,000 --> 00:00:15,280
And Mom and Dad will come pick you up
later, okay?

7
00:00:15,360 --> 00:00:17,720
No, why? I don't want to.
-I don't want to.

8
00:00:17,800 --> 00:00:19,360
No "I don't want to," girls, no arguing,

9
00:00:19,440 --> 00:00:20,920
You're going to Grandma's, that's it.

10
00:00:21,400 --> 00:00:23,080
Did you bring the DVD that puts them to sleep?

11
00:00:23,160 --> 00:00:24,880
Of course, "War and Peace" in the kids' version.

12
00:00:25,640 --> 00:00:28,400
Bedtime songs with grape jam.
-Very funny.

13
00:00:28,480 --> 00:00:30,480
If you had arranged a babysitter,
that could've entertained me too.

14
00:00:31,120 --> 00:00:32,640
This is your event, right? Not mine.

15
00:00:32,720 --> 00:00:34,640
What's your problem coordinating something once in your life?

16
00:00:34,720 --> 00:00:36,120
It's not that complicated,

17
00:00:36,200 --> 00:00:37,920
it's way easier than coordinating a crop-dusting plane

18
00:00:38,000 --> 00:00:40,040
taking off from Ovda Airport in the Negev.

19
00:00:40,120 --> 00:00:42,760
How did you get from the babysitter
to Ovda Airport in the Negev? Tell me.

20
00:00:42,840 --> 00:00:45,160
Just like you got from guava jam to Tolstoy, okay?

21
00:00:45,640 --> 00:00:47,360
I don't want to.
-Here we go.

22
00:00:51,920 --> 00:00:53,960
Look at me, look at me and...

23
00:01:03,800 --> 00:01:05,200
Shabbat Shalom.
-Shabbat Shalom.

24
00:01:05,280 --> 00:01:06,560
Have a good week.

25
00:01:06,640 --> 00:01:07,960
What, you guys are leaving already?
-Yeah.

26
00:01:08,280 --> 00:01:09,800
What, Orna and Moshe aren't here?

27
00:01:09,880 --> 00:01:12,400
No, they waited for you, saw you weren't coming, so they left.

28
00:01:12,480 --> 00:01:13,400
Why did you come so late?

29
00:01:13,480 --> 00:01:15,760
No, we just decided to stay a bit longer today.

30
00:01:16,200 --> 00:01:18,840
There's a reunion for my school friends tonight.

31
00:01:19,320 --> 00:01:21,320
A reunion?
-Why not?

32
00:01:21,680 --> 00:01:23,200
I'm in touch

33
00:01:23,280 --> 00:01:26,560
with three babies from my class at the health clinic.

34
00:01:27,880 --> 00:01:29,920
We meet once a month

35
00:01:30,440 --> 00:01:31,640
for a purpose.

36
00:01:32,880 --> 00:01:35,600
First of all, it's a concentrated school
and there's nothing wrong with that,

37
00:01:35,680 --> 00:01:38,000
you see where you are, where your friends are.
-Yeah.

38
00:01:38,080 --> 00:01:39,160
What each one has accomplished.

39
00:01:39,240 --> 00:01:41,800
How many kilometers you've traveled, how many you have left.
-Yeah.

40
00:01:41,880 --> 00:01:43,280
What each one got married with.

41
00:01:43,640 --> 00:01:44,920
To show off my wife.

42
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:47,480
Come on, Manny, what's up? We're waiting.
-Coming!

43
00:01:47,560 --> 00:01:48,800
Honestly, I didn't get it,

44
00:01:49,120 --> 00:01:52,400
what's the connection between you coming late
and having a reunion?

45
00:01:54,240 --> 00:01:56,720
We just didn't manage to get a babysitter

46
00:01:57,320 --> 00:01:59,640
and I thought to ask Mom
if we could leave the girls here?

47
00:01:59,720 --> 00:02:01,080
We'll put them to sleep,

48
00:02:01,160 --> 00:02:03,160
at a quarter past eight my friend, Tzvika, will come pick them up,

49
00:02:04,040 --> 00:02:08,360
by ten-thirty, eleven at the latest after the reunion, we'll be here.

50
00:02:08,440 --> 00:02:09,800
Alright, come on.

51
00:02:10,240 --> 00:02:13,160
If I don't have to change them
or bring them, then it's fine.

52
00:02:13,720 --> 00:02:16,160
Did you bring the one who puts them to sleep?

53
00:02:16,240 --> 00:02:19,320
From the DVD, I don't have my own DVD.
-Of course, relax.

54
00:02:19,800 --> 00:02:22,640
Ella, Maya, Daria,

55
00:02:23,280 --> 00:02:25,120
-Love you.

56
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:27,600
Bye, Mom, have a good week.
-Bye, sweetie.

57
00:02:27,680 --> 00:02:28,840
See you.
-Girls.

58
00:02:28,920 --> 00:02:30,840
Have a good week. It was, a big problem.

59
00:02:30,920 --> 00:02:32,320
Shabbat Shalom.
-Shabbat Shalom.

60
00:02:32,400 --> 00:02:34,760
What, are you coming now?
-No, we have some...

61
00:02:36,000 --> 00:02:37,120
What’s this?

62
00:02:37,200 --> 00:02:38,880
Rachel, what, didn’t any of the sauce stay in the bowl?

63
00:02:38,960 --> 00:02:40,400
No, nothing’s left,

64
00:02:40,480 --> 00:02:43,480
I put the last three triangles in plastic for them.

65
00:02:43,560 --> 00:02:45,000
You should’ve come earlier.

66
00:02:45,080 --> 00:02:48,320
Want some coffee and pareve cake?
-Hold on a sec.

67
00:02:49,040 --> 00:02:51,000
Mom, can I ask for something?

68
00:02:51,880 --> 00:02:55,360
I just chatted with someone
I’ve been messaging for over a month.

69
00:02:55,440 --> 00:03:00,040
Through a dating site, no details, just a first name.

70
00:03:00,360 --> 00:03:01,840
And we set up to meet tonight.

71
00:03:02,400 --> 00:03:03,400
Good luck with that.

72
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:06,480
I don’t know, I’m pretty skeptical
if anything will come of it.

73
00:03:07,880 --> 00:03:09,200
So what did you want to ask?

74
00:03:09,680 --> 00:03:12,240
Is there any chance you and Dad
could clear out the apartment for tonight?

75
00:03:12,320 --> 00:03:15,600
What, so we won’t sit in the living room?
-No, clear out, clear out,

76
00:03:16,160 --> 00:03:17,800
So you won’t be home at all. Is that a problem?

77
00:03:17,880 --> 00:03:20,280
Maybe you could go to a movie? I’ll treat.

78
00:03:20,360 --> 00:03:21,240
Here,

79
00:03:24,840 --> 00:03:26,200
I had something here...

80
00:03:28,280 --> 00:03:30,280
It’s okay, Meirav, it’s okay, it’s okay.

81
00:03:30,840 --> 00:03:31,800
Dad,

82
00:03:31,880 --> 00:03:34,080
Where would it be more comfortable
for us to put the girls down,

83
00:03:34,160 --> 00:03:35,440
in the living room or in the bedroom?

84
00:03:35,800 --> 00:03:37,040
I’m not comfortable at all.

85
00:03:37,120 --> 00:03:38,840
Okay, so where do you want us to put the girls down?

86
00:03:38,920 --> 00:03:39,960
You said by 11 at the latest?

87
00:03:41,720 --> 00:03:43,320
Bedroom.
-Bedroom.

88
00:03:43,400 --> 00:03:45,200
No, in the living room.

89
00:03:45,640 --> 00:03:48,120
No, bedroom.
-Final answer.

90
00:03:48,680 --> 00:03:49,880
Yeah,

91
00:03:49,960 --> 00:03:52,440
Okay. Where did you put the disc?
-In my pocket.

92
00:03:52,520 --> 00:03:55,160
Great, so take them to the bedroom,
get them settled, and put on Tolstoy.

93
00:03:55,880 --> 00:03:57,240
They’re...

94
00:03:58,920 --> 00:04:00,320
Shabbat Shalom.

95
00:04:01,000 --> 00:04:03,280
What’s with that dress?
-You hear that, Mom?

96
00:04:03,760 --> 00:04:05,440
The guys want...
-Grandma.

97
00:04:05,520 --> 00:04:06,560
What?
-Dad sent me.

98
00:04:06,640 --> 00:04:07,960
What, did something bad happen?

99
00:04:08,600 --> 00:04:11,120
He forgot a bag here.
-A bag? Where was the bag?

100
00:04:14,200 --> 00:04:15,120
Here.

101
00:04:15,200 --> 00:04:16,640
Did you take that for yourself?

102
00:04:16,720 --> 00:04:20,519
No, I just looked to see what was inside
to know who it belongs to.

103
00:04:20,600 --> 00:04:21,560
Of course.

104
00:04:23,800 --> 00:04:24,720
What?

105
00:04:25,080 --> 00:04:27,040
I’m not here.

106
00:04:27,120 --> 00:04:28,680
Good thing I remembered, Sali,

107
00:04:29,040 --> 00:04:32,640
we need to go out to a movie tonight.
-What movie, Mom, what movie?

108
00:04:32,720 --> 00:04:34,800
I really don’t need a movie right now.

109
00:04:35,480 --> 00:04:38,160
Where did you get that? What, do you have coupons for a movie?

110
00:04:38,240 --> 00:04:39,400
What coupons?

111
00:04:39,760 --> 00:04:42,880
Meirav asked us to leave the house because she has a date.

112
00:04:43,440 --> 00:04:46,000
With a guy?
-No, with a frog.

113
00:04:46,080 --> 00:04:46,920
Of course with a guy.

114
00:04:47,000 --> 00:04:49,360
Well, I have a date too, with my bed and my pillow.

115
00:04:49,440 --> 00:04:50,600
And it’s a double date.

116
00:04:50,680 --> 00:04:54,400
Mom, Shai and I really have to go today
so we wanted to leave the girls with you.

117
00:04:54,960 --> 00:04:57,760
See? It’s not working out, please.

118
00:04:58,280 --> 00:05:01,160
And I also said yes to them.
-Right.

119
00:05:01,240 --> 00:05:02,480
But I said yes to Meirav.

120
00:05:02,560 --> 00:05:04,360
You said yes to Meirav?
-Yeah.

121
00:05:04,440 --> 00:05:06,560
Without asking me?
-Why, because you asked me?

122
00:05:06,640 --> 00:05:09,880
They have a cycle.
-And she has a suitor.

123
00:05:10,840 --> 00:05:14,160
Sali, if you go out tonight

124
00:05:14,760 --> 00:05:18,960
it could very well be she’ll be gone for good.

125
00:05:21,280 --> 00:05:22,680
I’m sorry, find another arrangement!

126
00:05:23,320 --> 00:05:24,440
Wait, wait, wait, both of you.

127
00:05:24,520 --> 00:05:25,800
I’ll handle it, I’ll talk to Meirav,

128
00:05:25,880 --> 00:05:28,520
I’ll ask her to take her guy to a movie

129
00:05:28,600 --> 00:05:30,240
and you can stay here to watch the girls.

130
00:05:30,320 --> 00:05:31,480
I’m on it.

131
00:05:43,480 --> 00:05:45,120
Hey Shabi, what’s up?
-All good, Meiravi.

132
00:05:45,200 --> 00:05:47,800
I think we need to talk.
-Are you leaving me?

133
00:05:47,880 --> 00:05:49,640
What? No.

134
00:05:49,720 --> 00:05:51,280
No, no, no, listen, babe, listen,

135
00:05:51,360 --> 00:05:54,320
Shai and I need to go to a reunion
from Shai’s high school,

136
00:05:54,400 --> 00:05:56,200
but we couldn’t get a babysitter and I talked to Dad

137
00:05:56,280 --> 00:05:57,880
and he agreed to watch the kids here.

138
00:05:57,960 --> 00:06:01,440
Then I found out you have a date today.
-He agreed?

139
00:06:01,520 --> 00:06:03,040
Yeah, of course he agreed, it’s his house.

140
00:06:03,120 --> 00:06:05,640
But I’m his daughter.
-So what, Meiravi?

141
00:06:05,720 --> 00:06:07,320
What are you mixing up for me, meat, milk, and pareve?

142
00:06:07,400 --> 00:06:08,520
I invented pareve.

143
00:06:08,600 --> 00:06:10,560
You have kids, a husband, and everything,

144
00:06:10,640 --> 00:06:11,800
what do I have?

145
00:06:11,880 --> 00:06:14,440
No meat, no milk, just pareve.

146
00:06:18,960 --> 00:06:21,160
So what, what Meiravi, who’s this guy?

147
00:06:23,440 --> 00:06:24,520
What?

148
00:06:24,600 --> 00:06:27,360
We’ve been talking for a whole month.
-Nnnn.

149
00:06:27,440 --> 00:06:28,680
Until now we’ve just been texting

150
00:06:28,760 --> 00:06:33,280
but you don’t meet someone every day
who expresses himself just like you think.

151
00:06:33,360 --> 00:06:38,320
And there aren’t many people who use
emojis as precisely and smartly as he does.

152
00:06:38,400 --> 00:06:40,440
He’s not one of those who just throws them around,

153
00:06:41,000 --> 00:06:43,960
every emoji of his is perfectly timed.

154
00:06:44,040 --> 00:06:46,120
Seriously, when he writes haha...

155
00:06:46,200 --> 00:06:49,400
you feel like he’s really laughing, not just haha...

156
00:06:51,520 --> 00:06:56,240
Amazing. So I thought, like, I have an idea
how my girls can stay here

157
00:06:56,320 --> 00:06:57,560
and not bother you.

158
00:06:58,280 --> 00:07:02,160
You want me to babysit
on a date that’s really important to me?

159
00:07:02,240 --> 00:07:04,760
Think about it, how great would it be for you to see

160
00:07:04,840 --> 00:07:06,640
how he interacts with the kids.

161
00:07:07,200 --> 00:07:09,040
Haha... I’m not ready.

162
00:07:11,360 --> 00:07:13,320
I trust Shabi to change her mind.

163
00:07:13,840 --> 00:07:16,560
You’re optimistic, you don’t know Meirav.

164
00:07:17,040 --> 00:07:19,240
The chances are she won’t agree.

165
00:07:19,320 --> 00:07:20,560
No chance she’ll agree, no—

166
00:07:21,120 --> 00:07:22,160
I’m hungry.

167
00:07:22,800 --> 00:07:24,240
What happened? Did something bad happen?

168
00:07:24,320 --> 00:07:26,920
I can’t find the car keys, have you seen them?
-No.

169
00:07:27,760 --> 00:07:29,800
What’s up, Manny, what happened?
-He lost the keys.

170
00:07:30,480 --> 00:07:32,000
What’s the decision?
-You’re going to the movie.

171
00:07:32,600 --> 00:07:35,280
And the reunion?
-No, no, we have to find a solution with the kids,

172
00:07:35,360 --> 00:07:36,520
she’s not willing to compromise,

173
00:07:36,600 --> 00:07:39,040
she’s not okay with the kids being here
when she has this date.

174
00:07:39,560 --> 00:07:41,360
I don’t know what to do.
Dad, come on, what do we do?

175
00:07:41,680 --> 00:07:44,800
Why don’t you let us know
about things like this in advance, can I know?

176
00:07:45,400 --> 00:07:49,200
Why do you take it for granted that we’ll always agree?

177
00:07:51,000 --> 00:07:52,880
Maybe I wanted to invite people over today?

178
00:07:52,960 --> 00:07:54,920
Just like that, I feel like it, why not?

179
00:07:55,000 --> 00:07:58,040
Maybe I wanted to throw a surprise party.

180
00:07:58,520 --> 00:07:59,880
A surprise party for whom?

181
00:08:00,440 --> 00:08:02,520
That's the thing about surprise parties, you don't know for whom.

182
00:08:04,000 --> 00:08:05,920
Alright, we need to find a compromise with Meirav.

183
00:08:06,000 --> 00:08:07,200
She'll never compromise.

184
00:08:07,280 --> 00:08:10,680
That's why she'll never find a husband.

185
00:08:11,440 --> 00:08:13,880
Even with the noise from the hairdryer, she picks up the word "husband."

186
00:08:15,200 --> 00:08:16,080
Okay,

187
00:08:16,920 --> 00:08:18,520
Don't worry, I've got this.

188
00:08:19,120 --> 00:08:20,040
Stay strong.

189
00:08:20,480 --> 00:08:25,200
Fifty bucks she’s peeling his skin
and rolling it in salt.

190
00:08:35,080 --> 00:08:37,000
Meirav, Meirav, can I?

191
00:08:38,039 --> 00:08:39,919
Shai, I told them not to send messengers,

192
00:08:40,000 --> 00:08:42,600
If someone has something to say,
they should tell me directly.

193
00:08:42,679 --> 00:08:44,880
So here I am, I have something to say, I came myself.

194
00:08:44,960 --> 00:08:46,080
What?

195
00:08:46,160 --> 00:08:49,400
Look, I have something really, really important tonight,
it’s really important to me.

196
00:08:49,480 --> 00:08:51,960
Cycle, I heard you have something new?

197
00:08:52,040 --> 00:08:53,240
Yeah, an idea.

198
00:08:53,640 --> 00:08:56,840
We’ll put the girls to sleep before you came
and they’ll be here in the room,

199
00:08:56,920 --> 00:08:59,400
You won’t even notice they’re here, they’ll be out cold.

200
00:09:00,680 --> 00:09:02,200
Sorry to interrupt,
I think my keys are here.

201
00:09:02,280 --> 00:09:03,920
I didn’t see them, look around.

202
00:09:05,840 --> 00:09:08,240
And what if they’re not asleep?
-Don’t worry, they’re sleeping.

203
00:09:08,320 --> 00:09:09,800
Sorry.
-Sleeping.

204
00:09:09,880 --> 00:09:11,160
Block.

205
00:09:11,240 --> 00:09:12,360
Sorry.
-And the living room?

206
00:09:12,440 --> 00:09:14,000
It’s all yours.
-Hold on a sec.

207
00:09:14,080 --> 00:09:16,680
Until eight-thirty?
-If not, we’re taking them with us.

208
00:09:17,280 --> 00:09:18,400
Sorry.
-I don’t know.

209
00:09:18,480 --> 00:09:19,320
Sorry.

210
00:09:19,400 --> 00:09:20,680
I don’t know.
-Okay, sorry.

211
00:09:24,920 --> 00:09:26,720
Two hundred shekels.
-800.

212
00:09:27,280 --> 00:09:30,160
Meirav.
-And only if they’re asleep.

213
00:09:30,800 --> 00:09:31,800
Alright.

214
00:09:33,080 --> 00:09:34,640
He’s been there for a long time.

215
00:09:34,720 --> 00:09:38,160
I’m really sorry, I didn’t
mean for all this chaos to happen.

216
00:09:38,240 --> 00:09:41,320
A calm weekend only exists on the radio.

217
00:09:41,400 --> 00:09:43,360
Even if it seems like it’s in an instant!

218
00:09:43,680 --> 00:09:46,520
Just know there’s someone behind the door
who wants something from you.

219
00:09:48,720 --> 00:09:49,760
What happened?
-What happened?

220
00:09:49,840 --> 00:09:50,880
Did something bad happen?

221
00:09:52,640 --> 00:09:54,040
Mom, enough.

222
00:09:56,160 --> 00:09:57,200
So?

223
00:09:58,360 --> 00:10:01,080
We reached a compromise, the girls are staying here.

224
00:10:01,640 --> 00:10:03,960
What about me?
-You’re going to the movies, it’s all good.

225
00:10:04,520 --> 00:10:05,680
Sit, sit.

226
00:10:05,760 --> 00:10:08,360
How much for a flash at Meirav’s?
-800.

227
00:10:10,120 --> 00:10:12,760
Enough, sweetie, enough, what happened?

228
00:10:13,080 --> 00:10:14,800
Moshe the fool.

229
00:10:19,640 --> 00:10:22,040
Where are the kids?
-They’re at home.

230
00:10:22,720 --> 00:10:25,080
Why, did I need to bring them here?
-Not today,

231
00:10:25,800 --> 00:10:28,280
it’s a bit chaotic but another day...

232
00:10:28,920 --> 00:10:31,040
I’m sorry to interrupt, maybe my keys are here?

233
00:10:31,120 --> 00:10:34,040
I don’t know, try to remember where you put them.
-I can’t.

234
00:10:34,120 --> 00:10:35,680
What happened, Orna?
-Nothing.

235
00:10:37,600 --> 00:10:38,480
So what, did you guys fight?

236
00:10:38,560 --> 00:10:39,680
Sorry.
-Yeah.

237
00:10:39,760 --> 00:10:40,600
Sorry.

238
00:10:42,120 --> 00:10:44,480
Come on, maybe look somewhere else? Maybe in the bathroom.

239
00:10:45,160 --> 00:10:46,040
Okay, sorry.

240
00:10:49,280 --> 00:10:52,680
He wants to go again
to that ginger friend of his.

241
00:10:52,760 --> 00:10:56,680
And then I have to be stuck
with the showers, with the putting to bed,

242
00:10:56,760 --> 00:10:59,480
So I don't want to, today I'm 'going out'
while he's "stuck with the girls."

243
00:10:59,560 --> 00:11:01,920
